    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix RA response window setup for 2-step and 4-step random access\n\n### Summary\nThe `setup_ra_response_window()` function in `nr_ra_procedures.c` had multiple logic errors that caused incorrect RA response window calculations. This fix addresses issues in both 2-step and 4-step random access procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ra_procedures.c`: \n  - Fixed incorrect return values in helper functions `nr_get_RA_window_2Step_v16`, `nr_get_RA_window_2Step_v17`, and `nr_get_RA_window_4Step_v17`\n  - Corrected logic flow in 4-step RA section to properly handle extended response windows\n  - Removed unused variable that was causing incorrect conditional checks\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running 5G NSA mode with 2-step random access enabled, the UE would fail to properly configure the RA response window, leading to timeouts during the random access procedure. Symptoms include:\n- UE unable to complete random access\n- gNB logging \"Invalid MSGB response window value\" errors\n- Connection establishment failures\n\nThe issue is particularly noticeable with network configurations that use extended RA response windows (v1610 or v1700 extensions).\n"
}